d:desc.p:
To represent & as a data character, use
    named entity reference:
      &amp;

The < character as a data character must
    be escaped as:
    <lt;

To specify the character encoding used for serialization,
    if necessary, use XML declaration instead:
      <?xml version="1.0" encoding="encoding-name"?>

d:item.d:message:
Conformance checking for script
  language $0 is not supported;
  it might or might not be conforming.

Conformance checking for style
  language $0 is not supported;
  it might or might not be conforming.
